    --size: Display the total size of a container.

    --help: Get help for any Docker command.

    --detach, -d: Run containers in the background.

    --interactive, -i: Keep STDIN open even if not attached.

    --tty, -t: Allocate a pseudo-TTY.

    --name: Assign a name to the container.

    --rm: Automatically remove the container when it exits.

    --restart: Restart policies for containers.

    --volume, -v: Bind mount a volume.

    --env, -e: Set environment variables.

    --publish, -p: Publish a container's port(s) to the host.

    --network: Connect a container to a network.

    --link: Add link to another container.

    --exec, -e: Run a command in a running container.

    --attach, -a: Attach to STDIN, STDOUT, or STDERR.

    --detach-keys: Override the key sequence for detaching a container.

    --log-driver: Logging driver for the container.

    --log-opt: Log driver options.

    --cpu-shares: CPU shares (relative weight).

    --cpu-quota: Limit CPU CFS (Completely Fair Scheduler) quota.

    --memory, -m: Memory limit.

    --privileged: Give extended privileges to a container.

    --cap-add, --cap-drop: Add or drop container capabilities.

    --user, -u: Username or UID (format: <name|uid>[:<group|gid>]).

    --health-cmd: Command to run to check container health.

    --health-interval: Time between running the check.

    --health-retries: Consecutive failures needed to report unhealthy.

    --health-start-period: Start period for the container to initialize before starting health-retries countdown.

    --label: Set metadata on a container.

    --workdir, -w: Working directory inside the container.

    --entrypoint: Overwrite the default ENTRYPOINT of the image.

    --expose: Expose a port or a range of ports.

    --privileged: Give extended privileges to a container.

    --read-only: Mount the container's root filesystem as read-only.

    --tmpfs: Mount a tmpfs directory.

    --stop-signal: Signal to stop a container.

    --security-opt: Security Options.

    --attach, -a: Attach to STDIN, STDOUT, or STDERR.

    --isolation: Container isolation technology.

    --cpu-period: Limit the CPU CFS (Completely Fair Scheduler) period.

    --shm-size: Size of /dev/shm.

    --ulimit: Ulimit options.

    --stop-timeout: Timeout to stop a container.

    --dns: Set custom DNS servers.

    --hostname: Container host name.

    --mac-address: Container's MAC address.

    --oom-kill-disable: Disable OOM Killer.

    --storage-opt: Storage driver options.

    --userns: User namespace to use.

    --volume-driver: Optional volume driver for the container.
